,"F.A.Q.","i-lucide-message-circle-question-mark",{"id":126,"title":26,"body":127,"description":273,"extension":274,"links":275,"meta":276,"navigation":277,"path":27,"seo":278,"stem":28,"__hash__":279},"docs\u002F2.meetup-groups\u002F2.facebook.md",{"type":128,"value":129,"toc":264},"minimark",[130,135,139,142,145,148,189,196,234,239,246],[131,132,134],"h2",{"id":133},"highlights","Highlights",[136,137,138],"p",{},"The following Facebook groups are useful to find hiking\u002Fscrambling, and even climbing partners.",[136,140,141],{},"These hiking meetup groups are grassroots communities where events are organized organically by members rather than through any formal leadership.",[136,143,144],{},"There's no central organizer or hierarchy—just like-minded hikers coming together to share adventures, suggest outings, and connect over a shared love of the outdoors.",[136,146,147],{},"If you're looking for a flexible, community-driven way to meet hiking partners, these groups are a great place to start.",[149,150,151,167,178],"ul",{},[152,153,154,161,162,166],"li",{},[155,156,160],"a",{"href":157,"rel":158},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Fgroups\u002Falbertahikerstogether",[159],"nofollow","Alberta Hikers Together",": Dedicated to finding hiking\u002Fscrambling partners. ",[155,163,165],{"href":164},"\u002Fmeetup-groups\u002Falberta-hikers-together","More info",".",[152,168,169,174,175],{},[155,170,173],{"href":171,"rel":172},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Fgroups\u002F1835212146753367",[159],"Find Hiking Groups\u002FPartners, Alberta",": Also dedicated to finding hiking\u002Fscrambling partners. ",[155,176,165],{"href":177},"\u002Fmeetup-groups\u002Ffind-hiking-groups-partners-alberta",[152,179,180,185,186],{},[155,181,184],{"href":182,"rel":183},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Fgroups\u002F1409264842848628",[159],"Alberta Hikers & Climbers",": Not dedicated to finding hiking\u002Fscrambling partners, but the community is tight-knit and people use the group to coordinate activities. ",[155,187,165],{"href":188},"\u002Fmeetup-groups\u002Falberta-hikers-and-climbers",[136,190,191,192,195],{},"Difference between ",[155,193,160],{"href":157,"rel":194},[159]," and:",[149,197,198,218],{},[152,199,200,203,204],{},[155,201,173],{"href":171,"rel":202},[159],":\n",[149,205,206,209,212,215],{},[152,207,208],{},"The two groups have very similar goals and rules.",[152,210,211],{},"Find Hiking Groups\u002FPartners, Alberta has more members and is a bit more active.",[152,213,214],{},"Alberta Hikers Together encourages posting specific hiking events (come up with a suggestion you'd like to hike, and a meeting time), whereas Find Hiking Groups\u002FPartners, Alberta has a lot of posts about people looking for hiking buddies without specific hikes in mind.",[152,216,217],{},"Alberta Hikers Together is a public group, so when cross posting in different groups, it's easier to post first in Alberta Hikers Together, and then share to the other groups.",[152,219,220,203,223],{},[155,221,184],{"href":182,"rel":222},[159],[149,224,225,228,231],{},[152,226,227],{},"Alberta Hikers & Climbers caters to those with an intermediate to advanced skill level in either hiking or climbing.",[152,229,230],{},"The Alberta Hikers & Climbers community is more tight-knit, and not just focused on finding hiking partners. People ask and post about trail conditions, avalanche and crevasse rescue courses,\nscrambling routes, indoor climbing events, etc.",[152,232,233],{},"Alberta Hikers & Climbers is a place where you interact with people first (share tips, ask information, etc) to build connections, and then find hiking\u002Fscrambling\u002Fclimbing partners as a result of the interaction.",[235,236,238],"h3",{"id":237},"additional-niche-groups","Additional Niche Groups",[240,241],"u-alert",{"color":242,"description":243,"icon":244,"title":245},"warning","The author is not familiar with these groups. Please reach out if you can add more background information.","i-lucide-info","Heads up!",[149,247,248,256],{},[152,249,250,255],{},[155,251,254],{"href":252,"rel":253},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Fgroups\u002F1014690558664444",[159],"Women Who Hike Alberta",": A group dedicated to women.",[152,257,258,263],{},[155,259,262],{"href":260,"rel":261},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.facebook.com\u002Fgroups\u002F992840258554589",[159],"Banff And Canmore Hiking Community",": A local hiking community for the Banff and Canmore area.",{"title":265,"searchDepth":266,"depth":267,"links":268},"",1,2,[269],{"id":133,"depth":267,"text":134,"children":270},[271],{"id":237,"depth":272,"text":238},3,"A few solid options to find your hiking fam.","md",null,{},{"icon":29},{"title":26,"description":273},"xItbBr3mBs8kEVTkJxEC0mjsLXdSzBCnBgb3NK5w_KQ",[281,282],{"title":10,"path":20,"stem":21,"description":273,"icon":24,"children":-1},{"title":31,"path":32,"stem":33,"description":283,"icon":34,"children":-1},"Formal hiking groups on Meetup.com.",1773623246172]